description: Unique number to identify the index (case). In this version of the data without personally identifying information, the true case index number that can be used to look up a specific case is replaced by a random number that only identifies a case within this dataset.
A unique identifier (number) of a decision on this index. (Ex: '1', '2', ...)
What the decision was the result of (Ex: Reserved Decision', 'Courtroom Appearance', 'Arbitration', 'Petitioner’s Request', 'Marshal’s Request','Conversion Event')

Various details of the case (without personally identifying info). This column is formatted vary strangely in the original data, and at this time it is presented as-is here and will take some work to pull out useful pieces. In most cases values for this column start with a one sentence overview such as 'Judgment with Possession, with Warrant, No Stay/Issuance Forthwith' followed by some number of key-value pairs separated by newlines (eg. '.....With Prejudice: No', '.....Based On: Failure to Answer', '.....Liable: Jointly and Severally', '.....Amount: $800.00', etc.). The set of items and their order varies, and some are repeated, some even have further nested values.
